        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:22PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Curtis Station, or 12 miles west of Batesville, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Batesville, Marks, Sardis, Lambert, Como, Crowder, Sledge, Belen,
Darling, Pleasant Grove, Curtis Station, Courtland, Falcon, Mims,
Asa, Essex, Horatio, Cypress Corner, West Marks, and Riverview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
